beer.beer_description: The name Fjellbokk is a reference to the high mountains around our brewery in Flåm, and is a dark, malty brew with notes of fresh bread and chocolate. Brewed with fresh mountain water, this is a big beer inspired by the powerful nature around us. Enjoy this bock by itself, or with cheeses or dessert. Recommended serving temp 8-10 celsius.

items.badge_description: Thanks for staying at home, and checking in with Untappd! It allows us to stay connected to a community of beer lovers, just like you, even if we can't be in the same physical location. From our home to yours, cheers and stay safe!

While spontaneity can be fun, sometimes you want to make sure your adventure will rock. Checkout the menu at an Untappd Verified Venue before visiting and know exactly what’s on tap! That's 90 check-ins at venue that is verified. Try 5 more for Level 19!

Looking for more kick than a session beer, but want to be able to stay for a few rounds? You have to keep it in the middle. That's 230 beers with an ABV greater than 5% and less than 10%. Try 5 more for Level 47!
